    <date day="11" month="May" year="2016"></date>
    <abstract>
      <t>This document specifies an optional behavior of Transport Layer Security (TLS) client implementations, dubbed "False Start".  It affects only protocol timing, not on-the-wire protocol data, and can be implemented unilaterally.  A TLS False Start reduces handshake latency to one round trip.
	 </t>
